description:
Job Description

Be responsible for day-to-day schedule of the director;
Provide all-rounded secretarial and administrative support to the director;
Coordinate and accompany the director to attend meetings, conferences, PR functions and social events; and follow up relevant issues after attending the above events;
Liaise with different government departments, interest groups and media for the organization;
Assist in writing and preparing public policy related speeches, papers and submissions for the organization;
Assist in management of promotional materials and online marketing scheme for the organization;
Assist in event planning and coordination for the organization.


Job Requirements

Higher diploma or above in journalism, public administration, politics or other related disciplines;
2 years’ experience in handling public policy issues, fresh graduates will also be considered;
Strong awareness of Hong Kong’s current affairs;
Experience in media, public relation, and event management is preferable;
Thoughtful, attentive, detail-minded and self-motivated;
A good team player and able to finish multi tasks within tight deadline;
Good oral and written skills in both Chinese and English (Cantonese is a must), proficiency in Putonghua is advantageous;
Proficiency in using Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese word processing; and
Willing to work overtime and in non-office settings.
Benefits:


14-day annual leave;
5-day work week, bank holiday;
Contract-end gratuity;
Medical Benefit (both hospitalization & out-patient);
Compensation leave arrangement.

Interested parties please send your full resume, current salary and expected salary.

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. The information provided will be treated in strict confidence and be used only for consideration of your application for relevant / similar posts within the Office of Hon. Michael Tien and Roundtable. Applicants not hearing from us within four weeks from the date of advertisement may consider their applications unsuccessful. We retain the unsuccessful applications for a maximum period of six months.

Apoidea Group is an AI-empowered Fintech company. As the founding business of Apoidea, Apoidea Media provides content marketing services to financial institutions. We own 4 media pages - Market Digest, Business Digest, Health Concept, and Beauty Digest and run other financial institution client pages. Apoidea Media has been serving a large proportion of active Equity Derivative Product Issuers in Hong Kong.




We are looking for a passionate Social Media Executive to manage and create content for our Business Digest and Market Digest Instagram pages. 




Job Description:


Manage and create content for the social media accounts (especially on Instagram), including copywriting and image creating/editing;
Closely monitor social media channels for timely response to comments and inquiries from audiences;
Develop and lead all video content, including but not limited to script development, storyboarding, concept, editing, etc.
Ensures contents are original, accurate and fact-based Editorial in driving concept development and content direction for editorial projects;
Support the marketing team with English/Chinese language proofreading, editing, copywriting, original content creation and content vetting, etc.

Requirements:

Good knowledge or experience in copywriting;
Degree Holder in Design, Marketing, Business, E-commerce or related disciplines;
Experience in using Photoshop, Illustrator, Powerpoint, other design softwares will be a good plus; 
1 year of relevant experience in marketing, social media production, preferable in e-commerce industries will be a good plus while fresh graduates will also be considered; 
Familiar with various social media platforms (Facebook, Instagram, Youtube, and etc.);
Passionate, responsible, and flexible to be a part of the cross-functional team;
Excellent communication skills and strong problem-solving skills, able to work both independently and as a team;
Good command of spoken and written Chinese and English.
